  "texts": [
    "While there are many different ways of harmonizing data, they can broadly be described in two archetypes, merging and mapping 32.",
    "Merging entails developing a single global taxonomy or ontology that can encompass taxonomies or ontologies across disparate datasets.",
    "The benefit of this approach is that it contains all possible information across disparate datasets but the drawback is that it may be difficult or time-consuming to develop and the resulting ontology may be unwieldy or impracticable to use.",
    "For instance, suppose ontology A captures information on curfews, restrictions of public gatherings over 100 people and travel bans.",
    "Meanwhile ontology B captures information on lockdowns, restrictions of public gatherings over 200 people and travel bans."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "While there are many different ways of harmonizing data, they can broadly be described in two archetypes, merging and mapping 32."
  ]
}